parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Block Failure due to Poor Casting
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine block can cause coolant loss, leading to engine overheating, damage, and potential failure, which can result in costly repairs, safety risks, and even accidents.
symptoms: rust or corrosion on the exterior of the engine block.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil filter failure can cause engine damage, overheating, and failure, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks.
Failure of muffler hangers and clamps can cause exhaust system leaks, noise, and decreased performance, which can lead to safety risks and decreased vehicle performance.
Failure of the valve cover gasket can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and decreased performance, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks.
Failure of the timing belt can cause engine damage, overheating, and failure, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks.
Failure of the water pump can cause engine overheating, damage, and failure, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks.
Failure of the radiator can cause engine overheating, damage, and failure, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks.
The absence of lap belts or incomplete seatbelt systems can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as the shoulder belt alone may not provide sufficient restraint.
symptoms: Vehicle is equipped with only shoulder belts
no lap belts; incomplete seatbelt system; mechanic refuses to inspect vehicle due to lack of lap belts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Seat Belt Shoulder Restraint
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt shoulder restraint can cause injury to the driver or passenger in the event of an accident, as the restraint system may not provide adequate protection.
symptoms: resulting in injury; driver or passenger experiences injury due to ineffective restraint system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A poorly welded frame can cause the frame to twist when the brake or clutch pedal is depressed, leading to frame breakage, which can result in loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Unusual noise or vibration when depressing the brake or clutch pedal
visible signs of frame damage or twisting
brake or clutch pedal feels spongy or soft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can cause loss of stopping power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: brake pedal travels too far before engaging
unusual noise or vibration when applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Master cylinder failure can cause loss of brake fluid, leading to brake system failure, which can result in accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: brake pedal travels too far before engaging
unusual noise or vibration when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake light fuse failure can cause the brake lights to malfunction, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: inability to indicate braking to other drivers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause hot coolant to leak onto the floorboards, potentially leading to fires, or even explosions, which can result in serious injuries, accidents, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: hot water or steam emitting from the heater core
boiling water spilling onto the driver's legs
